Job Description

Key Responsibilities  Responsible for the timely and accurate month-end and year-end close for the management accounts, ensuring that the financial statements are properly supported and reconciled, and comply with Singapore Financial Reporting Standards (SFRS). Manage full spectrum of accounting functions, including but not limited to Accounts Receivable, Accounts Payable, General Ledger and Fixed Assets. Prepare adjustments to ensure that revenue recognition for projects with multiple progress milestones comply with the relevant accounting principles.   Prepare monthly, quarterly and annual financial reports. Prepare monthly bank reconciliations. Perform GST reviews and reporting. Liaise with auditors and tax consultants to ensure smooth audit process and compliance with tax regulations. Carry out ad-hoc duties when necessary.   Who We Are Looking For  The successful candidate should possess a recognised diploma in accounting or almost completing ACCA, with between two to three years of experience preparing the full set of accounts. Besides being a team player, the candidate should be a self-motivated and results driven individual who has a systematic and structured approach to tasks.  The candidate will be able to work independently under general supervision, with considerable latitude for initiative and independent judgment.     Work location: Near Commonwealth MRT 5 days work week   
















Company Overview



Teho International

                                                    Since our establishment in the post WWII period, TEHO Group has grown from a small local rigging and mooring company to become an international multi-faceted solutions provider, mainly for the Marine and Offshore O&G, and Real Estate industries. We excelled and stood out against the challenges in the market and dynamic economic environment through our focus on customer requirement, keeping abreast with market and product development, and emphasis on staff empowerment and development. Our remarkable achievement of significant growth and financial stability led us to list the Group on the Singapore Stock Exchange in 2009 under our holding company TEHO International Inc Ltd.

TEHO’s businesses include its twin engines of growth in Marine and Offshore O&G, and in Real Estate. Our global network has expanded from the headquarters in Singapore to Rotterdam, Houston and Shanghai, along with overseas logistics points and agents for our maritime business units. In conjunction with the Group’s

























