es, workflow, SLAs etc. and ensure that procedures are well documented **Basic Qualifications :** The individual should have strong client management experience, experience managing content portfolios (ideally with digital products), possess strong creative business acumen, exceptional interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills, and the ability to clinically project manage and work effectively under deadlines and in complex environments. The individual should ideally have previous management experience. Knowledge of the digital landscape is very important. In addition, a background in content production is desirable and advantageous as this role would work closely with external production partners, and our in house production team to deliver high quality campaigns. At Disney, having a diverse workforce is critical to our business. We welcome a variety of opinions, ideas and perspectives to ensure we continue to top our own performance and represent our global marketplace. When our people reflect the communities we serve, it enhances the way we connect to our guests, audiences and consumers. Together, we work toward an inclusive environment that fosters creativity, innovation and camaraderie across all of our companies. **Job ID:** 434589BR **Location:** Singapore,Singapore **Job Posting Company:** The Walt Disney Company    Maker Studios, a wholly-owned subsidiary of The Walt Disney Company, is a next-generation media and Technology Company and the world’s largest provider of online video content for millennial. Founded in 2009, Maker empowers online video creators and inspires expression. We pride ourselves on providing real value to talent and brands. Our goal is to support individual content creators through meaningful partnerships and brand building. Attracting more than 11 billion views monthly with over 650 million loyal subscribers globally, Maker reaches audiences across YouTube, Facebook and other platforms including the proprietary video platfo