oarding process and provide guidance, where required, to continue improve the overall client on-boarding experience.8. Support the rollout and commercialization lead in executing the internal and external communications plan, providing innovative solutions and best in class digital artefacts.Qualifications & Skills1. Degree or Equivalent2. A thorough understanding of corporate channels offering within SC and the digital transformation agenda currently undertaken including market best practices.3. Experience within a digital programme and a proven track record of participating in the market readiness / commercialisation streams of a large programme.4. Knowledge of web development technologies, including content management systems.5. Fully conversant in Adobe Creative Cloud (Photoshop/Illustrator/Premiere pro/After effects/Audition).6. At least 3-5 years of work experience in the transaction banking domain, with a deep understanding of the underlying products (cash, trade and securities services), regional dynamics and client segments to support the rollout to the SC geographic footprint.7. Prior experience in designing and developing digital commercialisation assets including user training materials, FAQs, client handbooks, product brochures & presentations, application demonstrations, video and online tutorials.8. Excellent verbal and written communication skills to prepare training materials and communication artefacts, effectively articulate the application features and manage / deliver product training sessions / awareness roadshows to internal and external audience.9. Proven inter-personal and influential skills to actively engage with cross-cultural teams within the SC geographic footprint to understanding their training and awareness needs, training the frontline country staff and clients, managing queries and feedback etc.10. Self-driven and highly motivated professional with a strong sense of ownership and a passion towards delivering high-quality outputs.  